{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[PASS 1 review — T11 Data-migration / backfill safety]\n\nVERDICT: T11 is LARGELY NOT-APPLICABLE / PASS. This plan's only persisted-format change is ADDITIVE and forward-only (a new `verified-at-sha:<sha>` manifest step + a queryable `verified_at_sha` ticket field), with no destructive DDL, no blocking lock, and no backfill of historical data. The content-addressed snapshot cache is regenerable/ephemeral (self-healing, reclaimable) — not authoritative persisted data — so it is not a T11 migration. One low-stakes coaching item (an ABSENCE: make the \"no historical backfill\" decision explicit) is offered below; everything else affirms.\n\nAFFIRMATIONS (criteria this plan satisfies):\n- EXPAND-CONTRACT / ONLINE (T11-a): The persisted-format change is pure EXPAND with no contract phase and no blocking DDL. Parent AC2 + S4 (ill-hazel-probe) design the SHA binding as a MANIFEST STEP, NOT a payload-schema change — \"no PAYLOAD_VERSION bump, no invalidation of prior signatures\" and \"prior signatures still verify\" (S4 AC1, regression test that pre-existing signatures still verify). `head_sha` audit field is \"preserved (additive)\". This is the safe expand-only end of the rubric. PASS.\n- BACKFILL / SCALE (T11-b): No backfill exists. `verified_at_sha` is set forward-only on new attested runs (set-once-per-SHA); pre-existing closures simply lack the new manifest step and still verify. There is no giant transaction or batched rewrite of historical tickets. PASS by absence-of-backfill.\n- RESUMABILITY / IDEMPOTENCY (T11-c): S4 AC3 makes the pin + field write idempotent and serialized via the ticket's existing event-append / optimistic-concurrency boundary (compare-and-set), \"set-once per SHA; re-verifying a DIFFERENT SHA overwrites (no stale/double pin)\" — re-runnable without double-applying. The snapshot-cache byte-total is reconciled by a startup full-walk (S2 janitor), making cache state self-correcting. PASS.\n- DUAL-WRITE WINDOW (T11-d): No backfill→cutover window exists (no backfill), so there are no rows-written-during-migration to lose. Concurrent writes to the new field are handled by the compare-and-set serialization (S4 AC3, proven by a two-writers-racing concurrency test). PASS.\n- ROLLBACK / DATA-LOSS (T11-e): Back-out is intrinsic — because the change is additive with no payload-version bump, rolling back the feature leaves prior signatures valid and the extra manifest step/field simply ignorable; `source=local` is the documented behavioral back-out (parent AC3). No destructive transform of existing data means no data-loss path on partial failure. S4 also retires the pin on reopen/abandon so a stale SHA never outlives its closure. PASS.\n\nFINDING (one — ABSENCE, low stakes; raised because the safe decision is implied but never asserted):\n- [ ] State explicitly in the plan (parent What/AC2 or S4 ill-hazel-probe) that EXISTING/HISTORICAL certified closures are NOT backfilled with `verified_at_sha` and require NO migration — they remain valid as-is and simply lack the new manifest step.\n  - criteria: T11 (a, b)\n  - location: parent plan \"What\" (attested bullet) + Acceptance Criteria line 2 (\"no payload-schema/version change; prior signatures still verify\"); child S4 `ill-hazel-probe` (30b3) AC1/AC2.\n  - evidence: The plan strongly IMPLIES forward-only/no-backfill — \"no invalidation of prior signatures\", \"prior signatures still verify\", `verified_at_sha` recorded on attested runs going forward — but never states as a deliberate decision that historical tickets are left untouched and need no data migration. A reviewer/implementer could otherwise read \"make verdicts reproducible + bound to verified_at_sha\" as motivating a sweep to populate the new field on already-closed tickets, which would re-introduce migration/backfill risk the additive design exists to avoid. Making the no-backfill stance explicit closes that ambiguity and confirms the T11-safe posture by construction.\n  - suggested_fix: Add a one-line note to S4 scope/AC and the parent's Out-of-scope: \"No backfill of historical closures: pre-existing signed verdicts are not rewritten and carry no `verified_at_sha` manifest step; they remain valid as-is. The field is populated forward-only on new attested runs.\""},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782531231866696001,"uuid":"56003d89-f58b-4303-af75-89a6e9ed9f76"}